HEADWORD: Petiole
<hw>Pet"i*ole</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*⟦omac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧tiole</ets>, fr. L. <ets>petiolus</ets> a little
foot, a fruit stalk; cf. <ets>pes</ets>, <ets>pedis</ets>, a
foot.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A leafstalk; the
footstalk of a leaf, connecting the blade with the stem. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Leaf</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A stalk or peduncle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petioled</ent>⟦br⟧
